<figureCitation id="269339F7FFEAB617B7FAFD71FECDFCCE" box="[159,303,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1832,1856]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,181,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[168,1418,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. A–B—Aemona infuscata Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, stat. rev.: A—phallus in lateral view; B—ditto in ventral view; C–E—Genitalia of the male and female Aemona gialaica Monastyrskii, K. Saito &amp; Vu, spec. nov.,: E—general structure of the male genitalia in lateral view, ♂PT; D—phallus in dorsal view; C—phallus in lateral view; F—the female genitalia in ventral view, ♀PT; G–J—Genitalia of the male and female Aemona tonkinensis Rothschild, 1916: I—general structure of the male genitalia in lateral view; H—phallus in dorsal view; G—phallus in lateral view; J—the female genitalia in ventral view, spec. La—lamella antevaginalis; Db—ductus bursae; St—sterigma" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556630/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">Figs. 11A, B</figureCitation>
