<subSubSection id="F6B276F9FFEAB617B7F2FCC9FB8CFBA6" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="BE172572FFEAB617B7F2FCC9FB8CFBA6" blockId="16.[151,1437,835,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B7F2FCC9FD0BFC86" authority="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008" authorityName="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,745,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infiscata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B7F2FCC9FEBCFC86" box="[151,350,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">Aemona infiscata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DA395883FFEAB617B60FFCC9FD0BFC86" author="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L." box="[362,745,835,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" pagination="287 - 291" refId="ref12280" refString="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L. (2008) Revisional notes on the Aemona amathusia (Hewitson, 1867) complex of taxa (Lepidoptera, Amathusiidae). Atalanta, 39 (1 / 4), 287 - 291, pls. 18 - 19." type="journal article" year="2008">Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B39EFCC9FEBFFC5A" authority="Rothschild, 1916" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B39EFCC9FA7EFC86" box="[1275,1436,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. tonkinensis</emphasis>
Rothschild, 1916
</taxonomicName>
. The status of the latter taxon was established by 
<bibRefCitation id="DA395883FFEAB617B4CFFCEDFAD1FC5A" author="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L." box="[938,1331,871,897]" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" pagination="287 - 291" refId="ref12280" refString="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L. (2008) Revisional notes on the Aemona amathusia (Hewitson, 1867) complex of taxa (Lepidoptera, Amathusiidae). Atalanta, 39 (1 / 4), 287 - 291, pls. 18 - 19." type="journal article" year="2008">Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii (2008)</bibRefCitation>
showing that 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B7AFFC01FDCCFC7D" authority="(Hewitson, 1868)" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[202,558,907,934]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amathusia">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B7AFFC01FE82FC7E" box="[202,352,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. amathusia</emphasis>
(Hewitson, 1868)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B50DFC01FCE5FC7E" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1916" box="[616,775,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B50DFC01FCE5FC7E" box="[616,775,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are separate species. 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B365FC01FB2EFC7E" authority="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008" box="[1024,1228,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B365FC01FB2EFC7E" box="[1024,1228,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">Aemona infuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B2E1FC01FEF7FC12" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B2E1FC01FEF7FC12" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The hindwings are ochreous brown and darker than the forewings with faint submarginal lunules. The original description does not describe genitalia. However, since the description of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B35CFC59FB42FC36" authority="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008" box="[1081,1184,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B35CFC59FB42FC36" box="[1081,1184,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">infuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we have been able to examine the genitalia of many specimens and find that the phallus has a conspicuous, sclerotised rib, the centre of which bears a few spines (
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFEAB617B6A4FB91FD84FBEE" box="[449,614,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1832,1856]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,181,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[168,1418,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. A–B—Aemona infuscata Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, stat. rev.: A—phallus in lateral view; B—ditto in ventral view; C–E—Genitalia of the male and female Aemona gialaica Monastyrskii, K. Saito &amp; Vu, spec. nov.,: E—general structure of the male genitalia in lateral view, ♂PT; D—phallus in dorsal view; C—phallus in lateral view; F—the female genitalia in ventral view, ♀PT; G–J—Genitalia of the male and female Aemona tonkinensis Rothschild, 1916: I—general structure of the male genitalia in lateral view; H—phallus in dorsal view; G—phallus in lateral view; J—the female genitalia in ventral view, spec. La—lamella antevaginalis; Db—ductus bursae; St—sterigma" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556630/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">Figure 11A, B</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B5FFFB91FCC3FBEE" authority="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008" box="[666,801,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B5FFFB91FCC3FBEE" box="[666,801,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. infuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only the distal margin of the clasper’s tip is covered by spines, while in 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B634FBB5FE0DFB82" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1916" box="[337,495,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B634FBB5FE0DFB82" box="[337,495,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">A. tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spines cover around half of tip. This difference, in concert with differences in size and wing colouration demonstrate that 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFEAB617B528FBE9FD56FBA6" authority="Devyatkin &amp; Monastyrskii, 2008" box="[589,692,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Aemona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFEAB617B528FBE9FD56FBA6" box="[589,692,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="502">infuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be elevated to the species level.
</paragraph>
